This paper is about generative neural models for constituency parsing, which is a task in natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. Within cs.CL, the paper involves machine learning techniques, so cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely. The paper also discusses the use of beam search, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (AI), so cs.AI is another possible sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves neural networks, which are a type of computational model used in many areas of computer science, including cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper involves image parsing, which is a task in computer vision (CV), so cs.CV is a less likely but still possible sub-category.
